- the first contract test harness lost the root $defs context while validating the manifest subschema.
- the existing OpenAPI example resolver attempted to resolve the new external schema remotely.
next_action:
- repair only the local test resolver context, then implement the minimum empirical gate behavior.

second_red:
- capture_contract_examples.py did not emit empirical-gate-response.json.
- the checked response example therefore was not yet proven reachable from the real CLI.

real_smoke_red:
- OpenAPI Generator 7.23.0 validate/generate/inventory/diff passed for the Go fixture.
- compile failed because generated tests reference an undeclared testify module.
- go test attempted a module download although the manifest declared network=false.
- cleanup left a 112 MiB read-only Go cache; it was reclaimed manually and residual count returned to zero.
- new RED tests require offline environment enforcement and read-only-cache cleanup.
